title: Beartooth Ride
description: A 25 Mile Hill Climb Up the Beartooth Pass.  With over 4200 vertical feet of climbing this race ends at over 10,000 feet
course: This years Ride Starts at Rock Creek Resort located 6 miles south of Red Lodge Montana.  Course starts with a half mile of downhill (the only downhill on in the race) before it the pass.  The first five miles of pass takes riders up the Rock Creek Canyon and is the steepest part of the ride.  Once out of canyon riders start to climb the switchback up the Beartooth Pass. 20 miles into the ride the course summits the canyon and the the riders tackle the last two climbs across the Line Creek Plataea at 10,000 feet.  The race finishes at the Red Lodge International Ski Race Camp at the east summit of the Beartooth Pass in Wyoming.
registration: Please registrar online at http://www.beartoothevents.com/.  Or the day of at the starting line.  Day of registration starts at 5:15 am.
notes: This is a hill climb in a time trial format.  Riders will start in 2 minute interval.  Road is open to traffic so race will start early at 7am
directions: Red Lodge Montana is located on hyw 212, 47 miles south of Billing Montana.  Once in Red Lodge Continue 6 miles further south on 212 to Rock Creek Resort.

title: MSU CX Weekend
description: Two days of competitive cyclocross racing in scenic Bozeman, MT.  A great tune-up for Rolling Thunder the following weekend.  The event is hosted by G.A.S./Intrinsik & MSU Cycling to raise funds for MSU\'s collegiate racing program.
course: Will feature natural and man-made obstacles on a contoured landscape.  Approximately 2-3 km course.
registration: Registration will occur on-site - unless otherwise noted on the flyer to be posted at montanacycling.net - from approximately 2 hours prior to the earliest race up until 15 minutes before the start of the race.  $20 per race or $35 for the weekend if both are paid for on Saturday.
notes: Prepare for Montana\'s finest weather conditions.  The race will go on.
directions: From Interstate I-90:  Take exit 309 (Main Street/Frontage Road).  Head west on Main Street.  Take an immediate left on Haggerty Lane before the first stop light.  Softball fields will be on the right approximately 1/4 mile up the road.

title: Woodland Cross
description: The race will be held at Woodland City Park in Kalispell on the 23rd of October.
course: The course is a mix on grass, asphalt, rock, hard-pack single track and stairs.
registration: $25 race day registration; open 8:30-10:15am. Juniors’ who are MBRA members - race free. USAC license required. Cat 4 men and women without a 2010 annual license must purchase a one-day license for $10. All other categories must have an annual license. Promoters reserve the right to combine classes.
notes: 10:45 race - Race Meeting. No single category payout will exceed $499.
directions: From Hwy 93 turn East onto Hwy 2 for 1 mile, turn Right onto Woodland Park Drive for .25 miles, turn right at Woodland Park

title: Helena Cyclocross
course: Course will consist of mixture of grass, gravel roads, and singletrack.  Fast and fun!
directions: Enter Lewis and Clark County Fairgrounds at Corner of Custer Ave and Henderson.  Registration is at picnic shelter on the left.
